\i0\fs24 \cf0 Page 20:\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\b0 \cf4 The progressive education both received from Parr seems to have taken fire at the French Revolution and driven them into contact with men from very different social backgrounds.13 Friends of Merry saw in this process \'96 discussed in detail in Chapter 3 \'96 a fundamental loss of social identity\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\b \cf0 Page 20:\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\b0 \cf4 A more precipitous descent can be traced in Charles Pigott \'96 tracked in Chapter 4\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\b \cf0 Page 20:\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\b0 \cf4 respect for literary talents with the pen did not simply translate into social deference\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\qc\partightenfactor0
{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "highlights://Print__Publicity__and_Popular_Radicalism_in_the_1790s#page=21"}}{\fldrslt 
