\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\i0\fs24 \cf0 Page 23:\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\b0 \cf4 This book understands radical culture as a complex and unstable field of forces, \'91fragmented\'92 as Mark Philp has it\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\b \cf0 Page 23:\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\b0 \cf4 Most historians of print identify a takeoff in the number of imprints from as early as the 1760s.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\qc\partightenfactor0
{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "highlights://Print__Publicity__and_Popular_Radicalism_in_the_1790s#page=24"}}{\fldrslt 
\i\b\fs22 \cf3 Page 24}}
\i\b\fs22 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\i0\fs24 \cf0 Page 24:\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\b0 \cf4 Print was often taken to be the precondition for discussion and debate.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\b \cf0 Page 24:\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\b0 \cf4 he understood the printing of the LCS\'92s first Address in 1792 as the moment when it became public\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\b \cf0 Page 24:\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\b0 \cf4 At certain points the societies seem to operate under the spell of \'91print magic\'92, that is, a faith that print could liberate mankind simply by bringing ideas into printed circulation.\
